This trail orders the active XanaNode implementation repositories by dependency and responsibility.

The protocol repository defines the canonical rules.

The Core SDK repository consumes those rules and exposes reusable validation, fragment, graph, and artifact APIs.

The Hugo repository adapts Hugo content and static publishing to Core-validated protocol artifacts.

The Workspace repository manages multiple local substrates and their operational workflows.

The Studio repository provides the desktop workbench for editing, previewing, validating, and navigating those substrates.

